com.ptc.core.components.tags.components

Class InitializeItemTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • SimpleTagSupport
      • com.ptc.core.components.tags.components.InitializeItemTag

  • public class InitializeItemTag
extends SimpleTagSupport
    This tag is used to initialize data for an object being created or edited in a wizard. Wizards with multiple target objects should have one InitializeItem tag per object unless the objects are all the same type.

    From the attributes set on the tag and the launch context of the wizard, the tag sets the properties shown in the table below in HTML hidden form fields and the HTTPRequestData parameter map of the NmCommandBean. For descriptions of this tag's attributes, see the Common Components tag library javadoc.
    Property Corresponding tag attribute, if any Form Data Key Description
    operation operation CreateAndEditWizBean.OPERATION_PARAMETER_NAME Operation being performed. Will be either CreateAndEditWizBeana.CREATE or CreateAndEditWizBean.EDIT.
    base type baseTypeName CreateAndEditWizBean.BASE_TYPE_IDENTIFIER TypeIdentifier for the base type. Used in create wizards only. This class will be the root type in the wizard's type picker. It is also used to look up the correct jsps for wizard steps that have different jsp variants for different subclasses until a specific type is selected in the type picker. If not specified as a tag attribute, the type associated with the wizard action will be used.
    default container none CreateAndEditWizBean.DEF_CONTAINER_PARAMETER_NAME For creation of WTContained objects only. If the wizard has a container picker, the default container will be used as the default value in the picker. If the wizard does not have a container picker, the default container will be used as the container for the object created. The tag will obtain the default container for the object from one of the following, in this order:
    • the value returned by the getContainerRef() method of the AttributePopulator class for the object, if any.
    • the container associated with the SubFolder selected in the launch page, if one is selected.
    • the container returned by NmCommandBean.getContainerRef()
    • if there is only one container in which the user has permission to create the base type, that container will be used
    type picker initial value none CreateAndEditWizBean.TYPE_PICKER_INIT_VALUE For creation of Typed objects only. This will be the default value of the type picker. Set per the "*Default Type" preference for the base type, if one exists, or to the base type, if not. Preference value may be a prompt, "blank", or a type name.
    type instance identifier none CreateAndEditWizBean.ITEM_TIID_PARAMETER_NAME For create wizards only. This is a TypeInstanceIdentifier for the object being created. If not passed as a parameter, a new TypeInstanceIdentifier is created. The type for the identifier is set to the type picker initial value if it is a type name. If the object is not Typed or the type picker initial value is not a type name, it is set to the base type. Note the TypeInstanceIdentifier will change if a new type is selected in the type picker. It should rarely be necessary to pass this as a parameter to the tag.
    AttributePopulator class attributePopulatorClass CreateAndEditWizBean.ATTRIBUTE_POPULATOR_PARAMETER_NAME The pathname of a class that should be called to populate attribute values in the wizard. Should be a subclass of DefaultAttributePopulator.
    object reference editObjectRef CreateAndEditWizBean.EDIT_OBJ_REF_PARAMETER_NAME For edit wizards only. A ObjectReference for the object being edited. The tag will obtain the reference from one of the following, in this order:
    • the value passed as the editObjectRef parameter to this tag
    • the value returned by NmCommandBean.getActionOid()
    • the value returned by NmCommandBean.getSelectedOidForPopup()
    Example:
    <%@ include file="/netmarkets/jsp/components/includeWizBean.jspf"%>
    .
    .
    .
    <jca:initializeItem operation="${createBean.create}" attributePopulatorClass ="com.ptc.windchill.enterprise.part.forms.PartAttributePopulator" baseTypeName="wt.part.WTPart|MyPart"/>

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false
